# Implementation Summary — Storage App Feature Update

## 1. ✅ Bulk Delete Multiple Files

### Backend
- **`fileController.js`** — Added `bulkDeleteFiles`:
  - Validates all IDs are valid ObjectIds
  - Queries DB filtering by `userId` (ownership enforced — no folder docs included)
  - Deletes MongoDB docs atomically with `deleteMany`
  - Responds `{ success: true, deletedCount }` immediately
  - Fire-and-forget background: parallel S3 deletes via `Promise.allSettled`, user storage aggregation, Redis invalidation

- **`fileRoutes.js`** — Added `DELETE /file/bulk-delete` route **before** `/:id` to avoid wildcard conflict

### Frontend
- **`Dashboard.jsx`** — Added `selectedFileIds`, `showBulkDeleteModal`, `isBulkDeleting` state + `toggleFileSelection`, `selectAllFiles`, `deselectAllFiles`, `executeBulkDelete` handlers
- **Bulk Action Toolbar** — Appears above file list when any file is selected; has Select All / Deselect All / Delete Selected buttons
- **`RecentActivity.jsx`** — Added checkbox per file card (hidden until selection starts); cards get blue ring on selection; clicking a card in selection mode toggles it instead of opening the file
- Two `ConfirmationModal` instances: one for single delete, one for bulk

---

## 2. ✅ Restrict Duplicate File Name Uploads

### Backend
- **`fileController.js` → `uploadInitiate`** — Added query before creating the file record:
  ```js
  File.findOne({ userId, parentDirId, searchName: normalizedName, isUploading: false })
  ```
  Returns **HTTP 409** `{ success: false, message: "File ... already exists" }`
- Uses existing `searchName` field (already lowercase) for case-insensitive comparison
- Trimmed filename before check
- Existing compound index `{ userId, parentDirId, searchName }` makes the query O(log n)

### Frontend
- **`Dashboard.jsx` → `uploadFile`** — Catches `409` and throws `duplicate:message` prefix
- Upload queue item gets `isDuplicate: true` flag
- Alert modal shows "Duplicate File" title (non-danger amber style) vs red "Upload Failed"
- Other files in queue continue uploading normally

---

## 3. ✅ Individual File Upload Cancellation

Already implemented in the existing code (XHR `abort()` on `cancelUpload(id)`). No changes needed — the existing implementation:
- Each upload has its own XHR stored in `uploadQueue`
- Cancel button calls `xhr.abort()` for only that file
- Other uploads continue
- Progress bar & status shown per file

> **Note:** The upload panel with progress bars, cancel buttons, and retry is fully operational in `Dashboard.jsx` lines 490–526.

---

## 4. ✅ Navbar Logout Button Fix

### Backend (`userController.js`)
- `logout` now uses `.catch(() => {})` to silently ignore stale session errors
- Passes explicit cookie options `{ httpOnly: true, signed: true }` to `clearCookie`

### Frontend (`Header.jsx`)
- Added `isLoggingOut` state
- Closes all dropdowns immediately on click
- Calls logout API but **always navigates to `/auth`** in `finally` — even if server returns error
- Button shows spinning icon + "Logging out..." during request
- Button is `disabled` during logout to prevent double-click
- Uses `navigate('/auth', { replace: true })` to prevent back-navigation to protected page

---

## 5. ✅ Sidebar Close Button Fix (Desktop)

### Frontend (`Sidebar.jsx` + `ThemeContext.jsx`)

**ThemeContext** — Added `isSidebarCollapsed` state + `toggleSidebarCollapse` function (in-memory, no localStorage needed)

**Sidebar** — Replaced the static dummy `<` button with:
```jsx
<button onClick={toggleSidebarCollapse}>
  {isSidebarCollapsed ? <ChevronRight /> : <ChevronLeft />}
</button>
```

Layout changes:
- `lg:w-64` (expanded) → `lg:w-[4.5rem]` (collapsed icon-only mode)
- Nav labels have `lg:hidden` when collapsed
- Tooltips (`title` attr) show on icon-only mode for accessibility
- Smooth `transition-all duration-300` on width
- Mobile menu still works independently (`isMobileMenuOpen`)

---

## 6. ✅ Premium Theme Security Fix

### Backend
**`userModel.js`** — Added `selectedTheme: { type: String, enum: ['blue','red','green','purple'], default: 'blue' }`

**`userController.js`** — Added:
- `getTheme` — Returns `req.user.selectedTheme` (from DB)
- `updateTheme` — Validates plan: `free/basic` → only `blue` allowed; `pro` → all themes. Returns **HTTP 403** if unauthorized
- `getCurrentUser` — Now includes `selectedTheme` in response
- Plan allowlist hardcoded server-side, never trusting frontend

**`userRoutes.js`** — Added:
```
GET  /user/theme   → getTheme   (auth required)
PATCH /user/theme  → updateTheme (auth required)
```

### Frontend
**`ThemeContext.jsx`** — Complete rewrite:
- ❌ Removed all `localStorage` theme reads/writes
- ✅ Fetches theme from `GET /user/theme` on mount
- ✅ `setThemeColor(theme)` now calls `PATCH /user/theme` and returns `{ success, error, status }`
- `themeLoading` state prevents flash
- Default blue applied immediately as fallback if fetch fails

**`Settings.jsx`** — Theme selector:
- Calls `handleThemeSelect(themeId)` → async wrapper around `setThemeColor`
- On **403** → shows Upgrade modal with "Upgrade to Pro" CTA
- Premium themes show 👑 Crown badge + 🔒 Lock icon
- `isPremiumLocked = theme.premium && user.plan !== 'pro'` for UI hint (display only)
- Backend is the actual enforcement layer

---

